4 SJR___ COMMENDING DREW AND LAUREN WENDLAND AS AMERICA'S TOP
5 YOUNG FARM FAMILY.
6
7 WHEREAS, commendations and congratulations are herein
8 conveyed to Drew and Lauren Wendland on being named
9 America's Top Young Farm Family at the American Farm Bureau
10 Federation's (AFBF) Annual Convention on January 12th in
11 Anaheim, California; and
12 WHEREAS, the accolade honors the Wendlands' impact at
13 Autauga Farming Company (AFC) in Autaugaville, Alabama, Farm
14 Bureau involvement, civic service, and agricultural
15 advocacy; and
16 WHEREAS, The Wendland family farm includes row crops,
17 cattle and hay, timber, a fertilizer business, and custom
18 work for neighboring farms; Drew and Lauren's most precious
19 crop, however, includes sons Mills, Smith, and Rhett; and
20 WHEREAS, the Achievement Award competitors are
21 farmers between the ages of 18 and 35 and have received more
22 than half of their income from production agriculture; The
23 Wendlands qualified for the contest as winners of the
24 Alabama Farmers Federation 2025 Outstanding Young Farm
25 Family competition; and
26 WHEREAS, based on a thorough application, they were
27 named Top 10 Achievement Award finalists during AFBF
28 Convention; an interview with a panel of expert judges
Page 1

Convention; an interview with a panel of expert judges
SJR14 Enrolled
29 followed, ultimately leading to the Wendlands taking home
30 the overall achievement as Top Young Farm Family; and
31 WHEREAS, as Achievement Award winners, the Wendlands
32 receive $35,000 toward a vehicle courtesy of Ford in
33 addition to the $80,000 prize package they received as
34 winners of the state contest; and
35 WHEREAS, Drew is Autauga Farming Company's Crop
36 Production Manager; he is known for shrewd decision-making
37 that maximizes efficiency, profitability, and stewardship;
38 Drew's father, Andy, and youngest brother, Dan, each
39 contribute to the farm's operation in meaningful ways; in
40 addition to support work on the farm, Lauren is a family
41 nurse practitioner in Selma; and
42 WHEREAS, ties to the farm community tighten the
43 thread of agriculture woven through the Wendlands' life;
44 they serve within the Autauga County Farmers Federation and
45 its Young Farmers program, plus national organizations and
46 state entities, like the State Hay & Forage Committee; Drew
47 is a graduate of the elite A.L.F.A. Leaders program Class V;
48 and
49 WHEREAS, the Wendlands attend Church Street Methodist
50 in Selma; they are exemplary representatives of what the
51 Young Farmers program stands for, faith, family, and
52 farming; as a fifth generation farming family they work
53 together to honor the legacy of those who have come before
54 them while also looking to the future; now therefore,
55 BE IT RESOLVED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA, BOTH
56 HOUSES THEREOF CONCURRING, That Drew and Lauren Wendland are
